node.text: Just a few hours before the @paralympics Closing Ceremony we catch up with @birgitskarstein - a para-athlete from Norway 🇳🇴 . She competed at Sochi, Rio, PyeongChang, and now at the Tokyo 2020 Paralympic Games, where she won a gold medal. Birgit tells us why the Paralympics are so important and how she is spending her time after the Games.

node.title: Chat with Paralympic champion Birgit Skarstein

node.text:
22 sports. Over 500 events. One Paralympic Games. Tokyo 2020 drew to a close today with a rip-roaring final few hours of action, full of dramatic finals and inspiring athletes pushing themselves to the limits. ⁠
⁠
India's Krishna Nagar claimed a surprise men's singles SH6 gold, while @TeamUSA defended their sitting volleyball crown from Rio in emphatic style.⁠
⁠
What was your Day 12 highlight? Let us know in the comments below.⁠
⁠
#Tokyo2020 #Paralympics

node.text:
Let's just take a moment to look back at the outstanding Tokyo 2020 @Paralympics Closing Ceremony!⁠⁠
⁠⁠
We are now left with the memories of all those athletes that pushed the boundaries to excellence, memories of those sportsmanship moments that show us that there is more to sport than just competition.⁠⁠
⁠⁠
To the para athletes, you are an inspiration to the world, thank you.⁠⁠
⁠⁠
And to Tokyo, Arigato, for a Paralympic Games that we will never forget! 💜
⁠⁠
#Tokyo2020 #Paralympics

He may be only 21, but @mondo_duplantis keeps raising the bar - metaphorically and literally. 🙌⁠
⁠
Early last year, the Swedish sensation broke the pole vault World Record twice and looked certain to take gold last summer. But the pandemic changed everyone’s plans - except Mondo’s.⁠
⁠
With his focus still firmly on #Tokyo2020, he created a makeshift setup in his back garden to keep practicing for when it mattered, and that commitment paid off as he soared to his first Olympic title. 🥇⁠
⁠
Hit the link in bio to watch his Olympic highlights. ⁠
⁠
#ShiningStars #PoleVault @sweolympic ⁠

node.text:
Iran's Morteza Mehrzadselakjani 🇮🇷🏐 at 2m46 is the tallest Paralympian of all time and the world's second tallest man. The star player helped Iran spike into Paralympic history with seventh consecutive gold medal victory, following the win over Russian Paralympic Committee in the Tokyo 2020 men's sitting volleyball final. 

Mehrzad, as he is known, was diagnosed with acromegaly, a condition that stems from excessive growth hormone. He normally uses a wheelchair or crutches to get around as a result of a serious pelvis fracture suffered in a bicycle accident as a 16-year-old.

“Before joining the sport, I was an isolated person,” Mehrzad said just ahead of Tokyo 2020. “In the past, I could never imagine such a future for myself, but sitting volleyball changed my life. For this reason, I call sitting volleyball a miracle in my life.”

Going out with a bang! The penultimate day of the Tokyo 2020 Paralympics saw no signs of slowing down, with exhilarating action across the board. ⁠
⁠
Brazil continued their startling record of winning every 5-a-side football gold since the sport was introduced in 2004, while Japanese badminton player Sarina Satomi wrote her name into the records books after becoming the first women's badminton champion in Paralympic history.⁠
⁠
What was your highlight? Let us know in the comments below as Day 11 ends and Day 12 begins, bringing a blockbuster Paralympic Games to a thrilling close.⁠
⁠

When the city of Tokyo was awarded the #Olympics in 2013, Kobe Abe inspired his two judo-obsessed children by stating he would love to see them compete at those Games. 🇯🇵⁠
⁠
Eight years later, his wish came true. However, the fairytale continued as Hifumi and his sister Uta shocked the world.⁠
⁠
For the first time ever, two siblings both won Olympic gold in an individual sport on the same day, sending not just their family, but the host nation crazy. 🥇🥇🇯🇵⁠
⁠
Hit the link in bio for the full story on this special day in Olympic history. ⁠
